============================================================
PYTHON PART 1 – EXPLORATORY DATA ANALYSIS (EDA)
============================================================

Description:
This section represents the first Python phase of the project,
focusing on Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) and visualization.

The datasets used in this part are the final outputs generated
from the SQL section (04 – Final Analytical Summary). These
CSV files contain structured and aggregated data, ready for
analysis.

Using Python (Pandas, Matplotlib, and Seaborn), the data is
loaded, explored, and transformed into visual representations
to extract meaningful insights.

The goal of this part is to:
- validate and understand the structured data from SQL
- visualize key patterns and relationships
- provide clear and interpretable insights at different levels
  (dataset, team, and matchup)


------------------------------------------------------------
Structure of the Analysis
------------------------------------------------------------

The analysis is divided into three main parts:

01_general:
Provides a high-level overview of the dataset, including
basic statistics, scoring behavior, and match outcomes.

02_team_perf:
Focuses on team-level performance, analyzing wins, win rates,
goal scoring, defensive behavior, and correlations between
performance metrics.

03_matchup:
Examines head-to-head matchups between top teams (Big 5),
highlighting scoring patterns, match intensity, dominance,
and overall playing style.


------------------------------------------------------------
Comment on Results
------------------------------------------------------------

The analysis reveals several important patterns:

- Strong teams consistently perform well across all metrics,
  combining high scoring with low goals conceded.

- There is a clear relationship between goal difference and
  win rate, confirming that efficient teams dominate matches.

- Home advantage plays a significant role, with teams generally
  achieving better results when playing at home.

- Matchups between top teams show different dynamics:
  some are high-scoring and open, while others are more
  physical and competitive.

Overall, the visualizations confirm and extend the insights
derived from the SQL analysis, providing a deeper and more
intuitive understanding of the data.


------------------------------------------------------------
Next Step – Part 2
------------------------------------------------------------

In Part 2 of the project, the focus shifts from analysis to
prediction.

Using the insights and structured data developed in this
phase, machine learning models will be applied to:

- predict match outcomes
- estimate scoring behavior
- analyze team performance patterns

This will transform the project from descriptive analytics
into a predictive data science application.